Error: Cannot find module '@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb'
Fix: Custom Lambda layer or use v2 of JavaScript SDK

https://apoorv.blog/lambda-layers-cdk/
https://github.com/bobbyhadz/aws-cdk-lambda-layers
https://bobbyhadz.com/blog/aws-cdk-lambda-layers
https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/lambda-layer-aws-sdk-latest-version/
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-nodejs.html

AWS JavaScript SDK v3 is not provided in Lambda so a custom layer is created to add it

Basically zip a node_modules folder as `nodejs/node_modules/` inside the zip

mkdir nodejs
cd nodejs/
npm init -y
npm install @aws-sdk/client-dynamodb
npm install @aws-sdk/util-dynamodb
zip -r ../package.zip ../nodejs/
cp package.zip /workspace/src/resources/lambda-layer/

